# The Qt plugins are taken from the official Qt binaries, and those link their own
# copy of libjpeg into the JPEG image format plugin. The plugin is not built here,
# so the system libjpeg cannot be substituted for the embedded one, and dropping
# the plugin would leave the application unable to display JPEG images.
ouaexp: embedded-library

# The application is a GUI program that is started from the desktop menu, and it
# takes no options worth documenting, so it ships no manual page. The tag was
# renamed, and the package is checked by whichever lintian the build container
# happens to ship, so both names are overridden.
ouaexp: no-manual-page
ouaexp: binary-without-manpage usr/bin/ouaexp

# The package is not going to the Debian archive, so there is no intent-to-package
# bug for it to close.
ouaexp: new-package-should-close-itp-bug

# The ICU data library carries no code and links against nothing, so it has neither
# dependencies to declare nor an soname. It comes from the official Qt binaries,
# which Qt6Core loads it through, and it is bundled as it is shipped.
ouaexp: shared-lib-without-dependency-information usr/lib/ouaexp/lib/libicudata.so.*
